#X text 28 17 In this example we combine keyboard tracking \, envelope and LFO as modulation sources. We now use [keytrack~] for simplicity and we combine its ratio output by multiplying it to the other modulation sources (all with independent modulation amount. The envelope and LFO amount are set in cents and converted to ratio. We're combining 2 detuned oscilators and using [moog~] with its internal drive parameter. This structure is a decent basic subtractive synth. In the end we add some reverb. Of course \, many subtractive synths also incorporate many effects like flanging \, delay \, reverb \, etc..., f 83;
